    "body": "Originally posted in https://github.com/starship/starship/issues/7158#issuecomment-3627314074 but I since I have also encountered a prompt hang, this should also serve as a data point here:\n\n---\n\nI have encountered a similar problem once when running `brew upgrade` and another time when running `albemic revision --autogenerate`. Looks like any subprocess that is able to run for a noticeably long period of time might be able to trigger this.\n\nOTOH if there's nothing to be upgraded, `brew upgrade` will terminate normally in a few seconds and the prompt works as usual.\n\nIf it helps, I'm using macOS 26.1.\n\n---\n\nUpdate: This is probably a macOS regression (https://github.com/julienXX/terminal-notifier/issues/301), if this is the case for you as well, it'd be better to audit all uses of notifiers so that the problematic cases are eliminated.",
